---
title: Fisherman's Shrimp Cioppino with Pickled Apple Salad and Garlic Bread
description: Cioppino (pronounced “chee-oh-peeno”), sometimes known as “fisherman’s stew,” is a classic Italian-American soup that hails from San Francisco. If you’ve ever had the chance to try it, you know that the broth is the most important part. It’s both rich and light, which makes for a can’t-put-your-spoon-down type of eating experience. If you haven’t tried it...now’s your chance! Either way, prepare for a flavor explosion. Our take is weeknight-friendly (i.e. doesn’t take hours) and features a bounty of tender shrimp. On the side, there’s warm garlicky ciabatta for sopping up every last drop of that broth, and a green salad with pickled apple and crispy Parmesan frico. Once bite and you’ll be hooked (line and sinker).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/2019-w31-r12-fisherman-s-shrimp-cioppino-76b93844.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/2019-w31-r12-fisherman-s-shrimp-cioppino-5d07ccddf65f90001159f2dd-007bc6a1.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/2019-w31-r12-fisherman-s-shrimp-cioppino-5d07ccddf65f90001159f2dd
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
